http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kozhikode/Safe-Kerala-drive-continues/article14017589.ece

As part of the Safe Kerala drive of the Department of Health, owners of 10 houses, five institutions and 4 shelters for migrant labourers have been served notice for creating situations that would cause contagious diseases as mosquito breeding grounds were found on their premises.In a pressnote, District Medical Officer R.L. Saritha said that department teams had conducted inspections in 3,418 houses, 49 institutions, 258 plantations, 107 construction sites and 38 shelters for migrant labourers in the district recently. A team led by Additional DMO S.N. Ravikumar conducted inspection in Vadakara municipality. The DMO has directed the health workers to continue the inspection.